                                cavern1

title "A Large Cavern"
descr
"This large cavern is a relief from the dismal waste of the swamp area. 
The
walls of the cave are smooth and polished with a bright and magical aura.
Ancient and mystic runes are barely legible along the walls and ceiling,
and
a faint trace of magic is in the air.  The only exits are a narrowing
passage
down or a tight passageway up."

names {"cavern1"}
extra {"walls","runes"}
"You observe these mystical markings which are geometrical in shape and
appear
to resemble the mysterious light in the midnight sky."
movement SECT_FOREST
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER,UNIT_FL_NO_TELEPORT}
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_MOB}
down to cavern2
descr
"Down here seems to continue forever.  This almost seems like it would
continue to the center of the world";
up to base_mount@deadl1
descr
"Up takes you out of the mystic cavern";
end

                                cavern2

title "A Smaller Cavern"
descr
"The caverns continue in a downward fashion.  More illegible runes are
etched in the walls. The temperature of the cavern is becoming warmer and
much more comfortable.  The feeling of magic in the air increases as you
continue the descent downward.  The cavern continues upward and downward."

names{"cavern2"}
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER,UNIT_FL_NO_TELEPORT}
movement SECT_FOREST
up to cavern1
descr
"The exit up looks to be a long passage out of this narrow cavernous
area.";
down to cavern3
descr
"The ceiling lowers as the cavern continues to the east";
end

                                cavern3

title "A Smaller Cavern"
descr
"You enter a long cavern which has an extremely low ceiling.  You almost
need to crawl through here.  The air in this place is warn and humid. 
There
is a strong  feeling of magic in the air and a pleasant aroma of sweet
flowers
emanating from the end of the cavern.  There is a crawl space down and a
passage leading up."

movement SECT_INSIDE
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER,UNIT_FL_NO_TELEPORT}
names{"cavern3"}

up to cavern2
descr
"This passage up will take you back towards the inhabitable area of the
world";
down to pal1
descr
"The path downward is a small crawl space that seems to almost require that
you
take off your armor to fit through.  It looks as if it leads to a wonderful
place.";
end

                                pal1

title "A Great Cavern"
names {"paladin cavern"}
descr
"You have entered into an immense cavern.  The most amazing thing about
this cavern is the lush vegetation growing everywhere.  Brilliantly colored
flowers, bushes, and trees cover the ground as far as the eye can see.  You
don't mind the humid air but you sense a strong magic which helps these
plants grow in the absence of sunlight.  There is a path off to the east."

extra {"path"}
"The path is a tiny well manicured walkway between the amazing plant life."
extra {"flowers","trees","plants"}
"Thousands of yellow, red, blue, orange, and green plants cover the ground
for as far as the eye can see."
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER,UNIT_FL_NO_TELEPORT}

movement SECT_INSIDE
east to pal2
descr
"The path continues east through the abundance of plant life.";
up to cavern3
descr
"The crawl space upwards takes you out of this wonderful place and brings
you
back into the dark caves";
end


                                pal2

title "Inside the paladin cave"
names {"paladin cave"}
descr
"The path continues along for a ways.  There continues to be the lush
vegetation all around and a small stream flows off to the side of the path.
Various tropical fish swim in the stream.  You are in awe of the perfection
of this mystical haven.  A hut rises off in the east."

extra {"stream","fish"}
"A small fresh water stream flows slowly parallel to the forest path.  You
notice hundreds of tiny fish swimming in the stream."
extra {"hut"}
"A lavishly build hut made of straw and wood stands off to the east. 
Wooden
steps lead up into the hut."

flags {UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER,UNIT_FL_NO_TELEPORT}

movement SECT_INSIDE
east to pal3
descr
"This path continues directly to the wooden steps that lead to the hut.";
west to pal1
descr
"The path continues off into the lush vegetation";
end


